Pleasure, Mr. President.

984
00:50:53,483 --> 00:50:56,316
And Jim Reston, one of my researchers.

985
00:50:56,386 --> 00:50:58,616
Pleasure to meet you, Mr. Reston.

986
00:51:01,958 --> 00:51:03,448
Mr. President.

987
00:51:03,527 --> 00:51:06,189
Excuse me, sir? Got a
room for you right here.

988
00:51:10,634 --> 00:51:13,899
Wow. That was devastating, withering.

989
00:51:13,970 --> 00:51:15,437
I mean, I don't think he's
ever gonna get over that.

990
00:51:15,505 --> 00:51:16,733
Yeah, fuck off.

991
00:51:18,308 --> 00:51:21,106
I got you guys set up back here.

992
00:51:21,178 --> 00:51:25,114
Now this is your green room.

993
00:51:25,182 --> 00:51:27,673
And the President will
be on the large monitor.

994
00:51:27,751 --> 00:51:29,446
Craft services is that way.

995
00:51:38,261 --> 00:51:39,694
Keep it about that temperature, okay?

996
00:51:39,763 --> 00:51:40,752
Mr. President?

997
00:51:40,831 --> 00:51:41,855
Yeah.

998
00:51:41,932 --> 00:51:43,297
Before we start, I just want to say

999
00:51:43,366 --> 00:51:46,460
how delighted we all are
by Mrs. Nixon's recovery.

1000
00:51:46,536 --> 00:51:48,436
Well, thank you. It's true.

1001
00:51:48,505 --> 00:51:50,496
She's much better now.

1002
00:51:50,574 --> 00:51:55,102
She's just getting round to the
business of replying to all the cards.

1003
00:51:55,912 --> 00:51:58,403
And from our point of view, well,

1004
00:51:58,482 --> 00:52:01,144
I'd just like to say how pleased we are

1005
00:52:01,218 --> 00:52:02,651
that you got this all together.

1006
00:52:02,719 --> 00:52:03,777
Thank you.

1007
00:52:03,854 --> 00:52:06,982
As I understand it, it's
been quite a struggle.

1008
00:52:07,057 --> 00:52:08,115
Well...

1009
00:52:08,191 --> 00:52:10,386
How much has it cost?

1010
00:52:10,460 --> 00:52:13,793
You mind me asking? Hey, come on.

1011
00:52:13,864 --> 00:52:16,458
Come on, it's just between us.

1012
00:52:16,533 --> 00:52:19,434
Very well. Two million.

1013
00:52:19,503 --> 00:52:23,098
<i>Two million? Jeez. I didn't
realize we were making Ben-Hur.</i>

1014
00:52:25,742 --> 00:52:28,438
But tell me something.

1015
00:52:28,512 --> 00:52:30,810
You raised it all now?

1016
00:52:33,183 --> 00:52:35,947
Not quite. But we're getting there.

1017
00:52:36,019 --> 00:52:38,510
Everyone's been kind and deferred fees.

1018
00:52:38,922 --> 00:52:41,618
Well, not quite everyone.

1019
00:52:42,926 --> 00:52:44,450
David, I'm gonna go
in with you on camera.

1020
00:52:44,528 --> 00:52:46,223
Excuse me.

1021
00:52:46,296 --> 00:52:48,457
I want to put a
handkerchief here, if I may.

1022
00:52:48,532 --> 00:52:50,363
Is that out of shot?

1023
00:52:50,433 --> 00:52:52,196
That's fine, Mr. President.

1024
00:52:52,269 --> 00:52:54,533
Contractually, I think that we made

1025
00:52:54,604 --> 00:52:57,903
an agreement that after each question

1026
00:52:57,974 --> 00:53:00,534
I might dab my upper
lip before answering it.

1027
00:53:00,610 --> 00:53:03,579
Which you won't show, you
know, when you cut it together.

1028
00:53:03,647 --> 00:53:07,139
You're probably aware of my
history with perspiration.

1029
00:53:07,217 --> 00:53:10,482
If you're referring to your TV
debate with Jack Kennedy in 1960.

1030
00:53:10,554 --> 00:53:15,321
They say that moisture on my
upper lip cost me the presidency.

1031
00:53:15,392 --> 00:53:19,522
People who heard it on the
radio, well, they thought I'd won.

1032
00:53:19,596 --> 00:53:22,087
But television and the close-up,

1033
00:53:22,165 --> 00:53:24,633
they create their own sets of meanings.

1034
00:53:24,701 --> 00:53:27,898
So now they insist I
bring a handkerchief

1035
00:53:27,971 --> 00:53:30,098
and that I have my eyebrows trimmed.

1036
00:53:30,173 --> 00:53:31,902
Sixty seconds, everyone.

1037
00:53:33,009 --> 00:53:35,068
You trim yours? No.

1038
00:53:35,145 --> 00:53:36,908
No, of course not.

1039
00:53:36,980 --> 00:53:39,448
Yeah, you're light-skinned. Yeah.

1040
00:53:39,516 --> 00:53:43,350
You got blue eyes. You've got no
troubles with perspiration, I imagine.

1041
00:53:43,420 --> 00:53:45,388
No, not that I'm aware.

1042
00:53:45,455 --> 00:53:47,889
You were obviously
born to be on the tube.

1043
00:53:49,759 --> 00:53:52,193
Stand by to roll tape in 30 seconds.

1044
00:53:52,762 --> 00:53:54,354
Settling.

1045
00:53:59,769 --> 00:54:01,669
Those shoes.

1046
00:54:03,240 --> 00:54:05,140
They're Italian, aren't they?

1047
00:54:05,375 --> 00:54:07,070
My shoes? I believe so.

1048
00:54:07,777 --> 00:54:09,802
Yeah, that's interesting.

1049
00:54:14,017 --> 00:54:16,247
You don't find them too effeminate?

1050
00:54:18,955 --> 00:54:20,422
No.

1051
00:54:20,490 --> 00:54:22,321
Well, I guess somebody in your field

1052
00:54:22,392 --> 00:54:24,223
can get away with them, you know.

1053
00:54:24,294 --> 00:54:25,886
Manolo, just check my collar, will you?

1054
00:54:25,962 --> 00:54:27,623
David, starting with camera two,

1055
00:54:27,697 --> 00:54:34,102
in four, three, two. Cue David. And...

1056
00:54:36,339 --> 00:54:40,935
Mr. President. Now, we're going
to be covering a lot of subjects

1057
00:54:41,011 --> 00:54:44,412
in a great deal of detail over
the course of these interviews,

1058
00:54:44,481 --> 00:54:48,383
but I'd like to begin
completely out of context

1059
00:54:48,451 --> 00:54:50,078
by asking you one question,

1060
00:54:50,153 --> 00:54:53,088
more than any other,
almost every American

1061
00:54:53,156 --> 00:54:56,319
and people all over the
world want me to ask.

1062
00:54:58,428 --> 00:55:00,293
Why didn't you burn the tapes?

1063
00:55:03,500 --> 00:55:05,331
Son of a bitch!

1064
00:55:08,138 --> 00:55:14,099
Well, Mr. Frost, I'm
surprised by your question

1065
00:55:14,377 --> 00:55:19,280
since we have an agreement, a
contractual agreement, I believe,

1066
00:55:19,349 --> 00:55:23,581
that we would cover Watergate
in our last taping session.

1067
00:55:32,896 --> 00:55:37,390
But if your viewers really
do have a major concern,

1068
00:55:37,467 --> 00:55:42,495
then perhaps I should
briefly respond to it now.

1069
00:55:42,572 --> 00:55:45,700
What probably very few people realize

1070
00:55:45,775 --> 00:55:48,005
is that the taping
system in the White House

1071
00:55:48,078 --> 00:55:51,343
was set up by my predecessor,
President Johnson,

1072
00:55:51,414 --> 00:55:55,544
partly to avoid the necessity of
having a secretary in every meeting,

1073
00:55:55,618 --> 00:55:58,143
and partly to ensure there was

1074
00:55:58,221 --> 00:56:00,712
a record kept of every verbal agreement,

1075
00:56:00,790 --> 00:56:03,759
no matter how off the cuff or casual.

1076
00:56:04,427 --> 00:56:07,021
Now, initially, on coming
into the White House,

1077
00:56:07,097 --> 00:56:09,930
I insisted on dismantling the system.